# Backend Task Completion Checklist

Before finishing a backend task, verify:

## Architecture

- [ ] Dependency flow is respected: Controller → Use Case → Repository → Prisma
- [ ] Use Case has no NestJS, Prisma, or HTTP dependencies
- [ ] Business logic is only in Use Cases
- [ ] Controller only handles HTTP and calls Use Cases
- [ ] Repository only handles data access
- [ ] Imports go through module public API only (see `core.mdc`)

## Code Quality

- [ ] No code duplication — shared logic extracted (DRY)
- [ ] SOLID and SRP followed (see `core/architecture.mdc`)
- [ ] No `any`, no plain `Error` throws (see `core/code-style.mdc`, `api.mdc`)
- [ ] No magic strings or numbers

## API

- [ ] DTOs for all inputs, validated at the boundary
- [ ] Correct HTTP status codes, `ErrorResponseDto` format, and typed exceptions

## Data

- [ ] Prisma Migrate used for schema changes (no manual DB edits)
- [ ] Queries are type-safe; no unnecessary `$queryRaw`
- [ ] List endpoints paginated; no obvious N+1 queries (see `prisma.mdc`, `performance.mdc`)

## Documentation

- [ ] README or architecture docs updated if structure or API contract changed (see `core/workflow.mdc`)

## Performance

- [ ] No unnecessary database queries introduced
- [ ] No unbounded list responses
